                                                List<String> clientName,
                                                List<String> userAgent,
                                                List<String> dctVersion)
                                         throws ApiException
        Gets the report of API usage metrics over a given time period. This API returns at the most 10000 results in the response to protect against the server running out of memory. Users might not hit this limit with the default report without any 'apiUsageReportGroupByParam' param but can hit this limit if the groupBy is by too granular like by 'client_name' or 'user_agent' only. Hence it is advisable to use startDate and endDate to 'limit' the scope of the report.
        Parameters:
        startDate - Report start date/time. Defaults to first API request. (optional)
        endDate - Report end date/time. Defaults to current time. (optional)
        apiMetricKind - Restrict the list to API usage metric of the given kind (optional)
        groupBy - The field to group results by. (optional)
        clientName - The Client names to be included in the report. (optional)
        userAgent - The UserAgent names to be included in the report. (optional)
        dctVersion - The DCT versions to be included in the report. (optional)
        Returns:
        ApiUsageReportResponse
        Throws:
        ApiException - If fail to call the API, e.g. server error or cannot deserialize the response body
        Http Response Details:
        Status Code Description Response Headers
        200 Returns a list of API usage metrics. -
